examples.en: He saw her and retreated, too shy to speak to her.
The rebels retreated to their mountain stronghold.
They retreated in the face of withering enemy fire.
Perry lit the fuse and retreated to a safe distance.
He quickly retreated from the room.
He had only contempt for the retreated.
They retreated behind trees for safety.
After her defeat, she retreated from politics.
Our government has retreated from its hard-line position.
The rebel army retreated to its bastion in the mountains to regroup.
The Canadian government has retreated from a plan to kill 300 wolves.
The once-thriving port of Rye was left high and dry as sea levels retreated.
The soldiers' encampment on the open plain was not tenable, so they retreated to higher ground.
